PATENT DEDICATION

Any patents that derive from, are embodied in, or relate to this
software — whether held now or in the future by the authors,
contributors, or the Zeblithic Foundation — are hereby irrevocably
dedicated to the Open Invention Network (OIN) and its licensees under
the OIN License Agreement.

We respectfully request that the Open Invention Network extend its
patent non-aggression shield to this software and its community to the
fullest extent of its portfolio and mission.

Patents exist to protect inventors from exploitation. They must never
be used to prevent people from building the tools they need to govern
their own information. This dedication ensures that Harmony's
innovations remain free for all to use, improve, and share.

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

ETHICAL USE APPEAL

This software is free to use for any purpose under the terms above.
No legal restriction accompanies this section — it is an appeal to
conscience, not a license condition.

Harmony exists to return sovereignty over information to the people
who create it. We ask that those who profit from this work honor its
spirit:

  * For-profit entities: Consider contributing 1% of profits derived
    from Harmony back to the Zeblithic Foundation.

  * Financial intermediaries: Consider contributing 5% of profits
    from transactions mediated by Harmony.

These are requests, not requirements. The code is free. The appeal
is to your better nature.

See MANIFESTO.md for the full vision behind this project.
